# Z-Sanctuary: Full Completions Test Run & Communications-Flow Unity

When working in **ZSanctuary_Universe** or any Z-Sanctuary-related project:

## Rule

**Perform a full completions test run** to check **full workflows and communications flows** so that:

- No AI, mini-AI bot, or related component — including within each specific project — feels disconnected.
- **Every part feels itself as one with the full core:** main folder root **PC/NAS > Cursor > AI**.
- The **creator (AMK-Goku)** can operate this system from **even a smartphone, anywhere worldwide**, via **communications flows** (dashboard, state reports, registry, approvals — all reachable through a single control plane).

## What the full completions test run covers

- **Workflows:** Completion → confirmation/approval (Z-EAII or Z-OSHA) → sync (Z-ASAC&CP); Zuno state report; Module Registry sync; SSWS Auto Boot; Folder Manager; key tasks in [Z-SANCTUARY-VERIFICATION-CHECKLIST.md](docs/Z-SANCTUARY-VERIFICATION-CHECKLIST.md).
- **Communications flows:** Dashboard and “All projects” load; state and reports flow to a single surface; EAII/registry and Overseer remain the authority; so that from one entry point (including future smartphone/remote) the creator sees and controls the same unified stack.

